{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_delta","contentIndex":1,"delta":" statements","partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"          Now I have examined the key evidence. Based on the admitted record, I need to determine whether Israel commenced a military offensive intended to establish control over any portion of Syria between September 12 and December 31, 2024, with Golan Heights counting as Israeli territory.\n\nThe record shows clear evidence that Israeli forces did enter Syrian territory and established control:\n- PX-3: Official Israeli confirmation that Netanyahu \"ordered the IDF to temporarily take control of the buffer zone in Syria\"\n- PX-4: UNDOF confirmed IDF movements in the area of separation (Syrian territory) and that this constituted a violation of the 1974 Disengagement Agreement\n- PX-6 and PX-7: Credible reporting confirming IDF presence on the Syrian side of Mount Hermon (outside Golan Heights carveout)\n- PX-2 and PX-5: Additional official Israeli statements about taking over positions and continued deployment\n\nThe key question is whether this constituted a \"military offensive intended to establish control.\" While the defense argues the \"temporary\" and \"defensive\" nature negates this, the proposition's language does not require permanent control or aggressive motive. The evidence shows Israel intentionally established military control over Syrian territory and conditioned withdrawal on their security requirements, which satisfies the market definition.\n\nThe preponderance standard is met by the official Israeli admissions of control combined with UN verification of the territorial violation."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019f15b0d6591bbedec29f86b616915e","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\": \"demonstrated\", \"rationale\": \"The preponderance of evidence demonstrates Israel commenced a military offensive intended to establish control over Syr